[SN]TITLE[SN]
Plea over woman and three children missing in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have appealed for help in tracing a woman and three children from the Pollok area of Glasgow who have been missing for the past week.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Kristina Pikse, 28, and her children David Hauberts, eight, Danius Hauberts, four, and nine-month-old Zana Hauberts, were last seen in Brockburn Road at about 16:10 on 26 August.
Police believe they may have travelled to the Blackburn area of Lancashire.
Despite extensive inquiries they have been unable to trace the family.
Ms Pikse is described as having long dark hair, brown eyes and sallow skin and is very slim.
David is described as having dark hair, brown eyes and sallow skin. He was last seen wearing black jeans and a white polo shirt.
Danius is described as having dark hair, with two lines shaved into the right side of his head, brown eyes and sallow skin. He was last seen wearing jeans and a brown/green jumper.
Zana is described as having dark hair, brown eyes and sallow skin. She was last seen wearing a white dress with Minnie Mouse on it and a pink cardigan.
Anyone who has seen the family, or knows of their whereabouts, is asked to contact police.
